def: Having numerous spines, as certain fishes.
A serpent, or serpent's head and neck, represented on the frontof the headdresses of divinities and sovereigns as an emblem ofsupreme power.
Attracting; adapted to gain favor; charming; as, a winningaddress. "Each mild and winning note." Keble.
A vessel; a duct. Vas deferens; pl. Vasa deferentia. Etym: [L.vas vessel + deferens carrying down.] (Anat.) The excretory duct of atesticle; a spermatic duct.

A name applied to several distinct fishes: (a) The garfish(Tylosurus, or Belone, longirostris) and allied species. (b) Thesaury, a slender fish of the Atlantic coast (Scomberesox saurus). (c)The Tetrapturus albidus, a large oceanic species related to theswordfish; the spearfish. (d) The American fresh-water garpike(Lepidosteus osseus).
A female ambassador; also, the wife of an ambassador. Prescott.
The evil and malicious disposition of Satan; a diabolicalsprit. [R.]
